= <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> Leader Ernst Röhm's Homosexuality Exposed

Wilhelm Abegg from the Prussian Ministry of the Interior has approached the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> and informed us about three letters written by <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> leader Ernst Röhm to Berlin nerve specialist Karl-Günther Heimsoth during his self-imposed exile in Bolivia. These letters, confiscated by the Prussian state police, are notable not for their political content but for Röhm’s candid discussions about his homosexuality—potentially exposing him to legal action.

Röhm has never concealed his homosexuality, and Hitler has never taken offense at it. Despite Röhm facing multiple prosecutions under Paragraph 175 in the past, none have been successful. However, this time we now have definitive proof.

What shall be our next move regarding these letters?

> *"We oppose the disgraceful Paragraph 175 wherever we can; therefore we must not join the choir of those among us who want to banish a man from society because he is homosexual".*

 - Die Weltbühne, German weekly magazine

