With definitive proof of Röhm violating Paragraph 175, the law criminalizing homosexual acts, we have been able to initiate legal action against him once more. Röhm is unable to deny the authenticity of the letters, and many have taken that as confirmation of their legitimacy.

In the end, Röhm has been convicted under Paragraph 175 and sentenced to one year in prison. This has brought the scandal back into the spotlight, severely damaging the public perception of the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> and <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span>.